There is a quick and easy way to add BusinessTech – South Africa’s biggest business news website – to your smartphone home screen. Android and iPhone users can get BusinessTech on their phone as a progressive web app. This allows you to quickly open BusinessTech like you would an app, without having to use a web browser and navigate to the site. The progressive web app provides many benefits, while remaining lightweight and not taking up much storage space – it is well under 1MB in size. Users also do not have to create an account or sign in to use the app – it is completely free to use and gives you full access to BusinessTech. As stated by Google, progressive web apps provide an experience users love, combining the latest web features with native-like app capabilities and reliability. To get the BusinessTech progressive web app, follows the steps below. When on the BusinessTech site in your Chrome browser, tap on the top right overflow button (three vertical dots) and select Add to Home Screen. It is as simple as that – the site will now join other apps on your home screen. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-403023" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Android.jpg" alt="Android" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Android.jpg 800w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Android-300x225.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Android-768x576.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> On your iPhone, open BusinessTech in the Safari browser. At the bottom of the screen on the browser toolbar, tap the Share button (rectangle with the arrow pointing upward). You then tap the Add to Home Screen option. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-403025" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/iOS.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/iOS.jpg 800w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/iOS-300x225.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/iOS-768x576.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> This article was published in partnership with BusinessTech.